      "body" : "<code>List&lt;HasWord&gt;</code> is exactly what you describe: A list which contains any objects <code>x</code> for which <code>x instanceof HasWord</code> returns true, and <code>null</code>. You don&#39;t need a wildcard for this. The wildcard means that it actually can be a list of another type, too, as long as this type is a subtype of <code>HasWord</code>.  (Sorry for the late comment.)"
