    "question_id" : 3009745,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>A question mark is a signifier for 'any type'.  <code>?</code> alone means </p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Any type extending <code>Object</code> (including <code>Object</code>)</p>\n</blockquote>\n\n<p>while your example above means </p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Any type extending or implementing\n  <code>HasWord</code> (including <code>HasWord</code> if\n  <code>HasWord</code> is a non-abstract class)</p>\n</blockquote>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 295869,
        "reputation" : 75003,
        "user_id" : 600500,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 54,
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/5925786f174975db18cbc83dd85e5c1d?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
